<TITLE> Govt introducing Primary Terminal Exams in December </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)--The government is introducing new public examinations -- Primary Terminal Examination -- in grade 5 from the current year, an official said on Monday. "The examinations are going to be held in December this year," information officer at the primary and mass education ministry Al Mahmud Hassan said to bdnews24.com. The cabinet has approved the agenda for clearance at a regular cabinet meeting on Monday, the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad said. Hassan added that the exams would be held centrally and the primary scholarship would be given based on the exams. No scholarship examinations will be taken separately from now, the official said. "Students will be given a certificate based on the results that will be required while they will get admitted in class 6," he added. bdne
